OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FService charge: India bans 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fservice charge at hotels   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fand restaurants            
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, India's consumer protection authority  
OL,6, has banned hotels and restaurants from 
OL,7, levying a service charge on bills.     
OL,9,FThe order came after authorities said  
OL,10,Fthere had been an increase in          
OL,11,Fcomplaints by customers being forced to
OL,12,Fpay the charge.                        
OL,14,FRestaurants often add a 5% to 15% tip  
OL,15,Fto a customer's bill under a "service  
OL,16,Fcharge" category.                      
OL,18,FBut new rules say restaurants can no   
OL,19,Flonger "add service charge by default  
OL,20,For automatically" to the bill.         
